cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO 

The paper deals with computer vision and graphics, specifically in the context of pedestrian detection and pose estimation. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely category. The use of computer graphics rendering to generate synthetic data suggests that cs.GR (Graphics) is also a likely category. The use of neural networks for detection and segmentation suggests cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) as possible categories. Finally, the application of the proposed method to robotics and autonomous vehicles suggests cs.RO (Robotics) as a possible category.
